git config --global user.name "enter_name_here" //sets user name

git config --global user.email "enter_email_here" //sets email

git config --global credential.helper cache //start config of cache

git config --global credential.helper 'cache --timeout=3600' //timeout password every hour

To setup a file in git create repo online with gui
Create directory on hard disk
Change directory on hard disk

git init //grabs files from git

touch README //creates readme file on disk

git add README //prepare to upload file

git commit -m 'first commit' //type revision

git remote add origin https://gitub.com/"user_name"/Hello-World.git //tell where your uploading

git push origin master //push file to web

Tada your done

Linky: https://help.github.com/articles/create-a-repo
